summary: The National University eLibrary provides access to various resources including e-journal and e-book databases, open access theses, and faculty publications. Key databases include Hindawi Publishing, PubMed Central, and Directory of Open Access Books. The library catalog allows users to search by title, author, subject, and more. Faculty publications are categorized by colleges such as Medicine and Health Sciences, Pharmacy, and Engineering. The site also features search engines like Google Scholar and CORE for academic research. Users can refine searches by availability, authors, collections, and item types.
